<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 4:48PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Catawba and east
central Burke Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 447 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Hickory, or near Mountain View, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hickory, Newton, St. Stephens, Conover, Longview, Maiden, Hildebran,
Claremont, and Catawba.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
